<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,151,1580]" box="[198,920,1340,1364]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Tarsal claws: slightly widened at base, but without a basal tooth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[151,1436,151,1580]" box="[199,435,1375,1399]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[325,422,1375,1399]" captionStart="FIGURES 164–170" captionStartId="99.[151,257,1918,1939]" captionTargetBox="[217,1379,205,1871]" captionTargetId="figure-81@99.[198,1394,191,1899]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 164–170. Melobasis spp. formosa species group aedeagi: 164. M. burnsi sp. n. (paratype, 26 km S. of Menzies); 165. M. formosa Carter (Cue, W.A.); 166. M. brevis sp. n. (holotype, Wurarga, W.A.); 167. M. dividua sp. n. (holotype, Wurarga, W.A.); 168. M. marlooensis Carter (Wurarga, W.A.); 169. M. brittoni sp. n. (paratype, Ankertell, W.A.); 170. M. flexa sp. n. (Bencubbin, W.A.). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Fig. 165</figureCitation>
